"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-news-world-1927049-olympic-games-paris-airport-strikes-opening-ceremony\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  An airports union in Paris has announced it will hold strike action on July 26, the opening day of the city'sOlympic Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 125, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23, \"end\": 28, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999987715, \"rank\": 1.2286134040843577e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The union - Force Ouvri\\u00e8re-is demanding more pay concessions as employees are \\\"dissatisfied\\\"with negotiations so far.\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 244, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The walkout will take place from 5am on Friday July 26 to 7am on Saturday July 27.\", \"from\": 246, \"to\": 328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This comes as air traffic at the Paris-Charles-de-Gaulle, Orly and Beauvais airports will be suspended for the opening ceremony on Friday.\", \"from\": 330, \"to\": 468, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A deal had been reached between the airport staff and their employers last week, with the union announcing that the strike action was now off.\", \"from\": 470, \"to\": 612, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not miss:ISIS is earmarking two major events in France for 'attack' as security ramps up    At the time, Rachid Eddaidj, secretary general of the CFDT union's branch at Paris Airports (ADP), said: \\\"We are lifting the strike warning, there is a majority deal.\\\"\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 626, \"end\": 630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2206189226957643e-19, \"text\": \"ISIS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\"}, {\"begin\": 665, \"end\": 671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9617909753220965, \"rank\": 0.03032601261221319, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 763, \"end\": 767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Democratic_Confederation_of_Labour\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CFDT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q178790\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Democratic_Confederation_of_Labour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Democratic_Confederation_of_Labour\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Charles de Gaulle is expecting peaks of 300,000 travellers passing through in a single day ahead of the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 878, \"end\": 895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_de_Gaulle_Airport\", \"score\": 0.9999999989681783, \"rank\": 1.0318805630487412e-09, \"text\": \"Charles de Gaulle\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_de_Gaulle_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_de_Gaulle_Airport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As France prepares to host the games in its capital, it has had to deal with a number of logistical and security concerns prior to the event.\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1001, \"end\": 1007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9617909753220965, \"rank\": 0.03032601261221319, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony, and many events, will be held in the River Seine, which has been subject to a huge cleaning operation to make sure the water is safe.\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1296, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1200, \"end\": 1211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Amid the threat of terror attacks, around 35,000 police officers will be deployed in Paris each day during the Games while 45,000 will be on duty for the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1383, \"end\": 1388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999987715, \"rank\": 1.2286134040843577e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not miss:Nightmare for Macron as Paris Olympics in 'crisis' after new strikes announced  Do not miss:Olympics 2024 star tests out 'anti-sex beds' and posts video on social media  Do not miss:Paris Olympics chaos as half a million tickets still unsold ahead of Games    Paris will also have 10,000 soldiers and 1,800 police officers from abroad helping with security.\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1507, \"end\": 1521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1665, \"end\": 1679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1743, \"end\": 1748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999987715, \"rank\": 1.2286134040843577e-09, \"text\":